Sports Field Holdings, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 12:42 PM ET
Leisure Products

Company Overview of Sports Field Holdings, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Sports Field Holdings, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the design, engineering, and construction of athletic fields and facilities, and sports complexes. It develops, sells, and installs PrimePlay line of synthetic turf products and track products, infill materials, and shock/drainage pads; and Replicated Grass synthetic turf systems. The company markets its products and services to colleges, universities, high schools, primary schools, municipal parks and recreations departments, and commercial and residential landscaping, as well as golf and golf related activities; and private club sports associations and independent athletic training facilities. Sports Field Holdings, In...
Sports Field Holdings, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the design, engineering, and construction of athletic fields and facilities, and sports complexes. It develops, sells, and installs PrimePlay line of synthetic turf products and track products, infill materials, and shock/drainage pads; and Replicated Grass synthetic turf systems. The company markets its products and services to colleges, universities, high schools, primary schools, municipal parks and recreations departments, and commercial and residential landscaping, as well as golf and golf related activities; and private club sports associations and independent athletic training facilities. Sports Field Holdings, Inc. was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Warrenville, Illinois.
Detailed Description


4320 Winfield RoadSuite 200Warrenville, IL 60555United StatesFounded in 20116 Employees



Phone: 978-914-7570

 www.firstform.com







Key Executives for Sports Field Holdings, Inc.




Mr. Jeromy Slade Olson


      	Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
      


Age: 47
        

Total Annual Compensation: $120.0K





Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2016. 

Sports Field Holdings, Inc. Key Developments

Sports Field Holdings, Inc. Appoints Tom Minichiello to its Board of Directors
May 17 17
Sports Field Holdings, Inc. entered into a director agreement with Tom Minichiello, concurrent with Mr. Minichiello’s appointment to the board of directors of the company effective May 15, 2017. The director agreement may, at the option of the board, be automatically renewed on such date that Mr. Minichiello is re-elected to the board. Tom Minichiello is currently Senior Vice President, Chief Financial Officer, Treasurer, and Secretary for Westell Technologies, positions he has held since July, 2013. He is responsible for finance, information technology, human resources, legal, contract administration, real estate, and corporate communications.


Sports Field Holdings, Inc. announced delayed 10-Q filing
May 15 17
On 05/15/2017, Sports Field Holdings, Inc. announced that they will be unable to file their next 10-Q by the deadline required by the SEC.


Sports Field Holdings, Inc. Auditor Raises 'Going Concern' Doubt
Mar 31 17
Sports Field Holdings, Inc. filed its 10-K on Mar 31, 2017 for the period ending Dec 31, 2016. In this report its auditor, Rosenberg Rich Baker Berman & Company, gave an unqualified opinion expressing doubt that the company can continue as a going concern.


